  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/alternatives.css">

  <script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@graph": [
      {
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
          { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://stackarchitect.xyz/" },
          { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Klaviyo vs Systeme.io", "item": canonical }
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": canonical + "#webpage",
        "url": canonical,
        "name": title,
        "description": description,
        "inLanguage": "en-GB",
        "dateModified": dateModified,
        "isPartOf": { "@id": "https://stackarchitect.xyz/#website" }
      },
      {
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is Systeme.io a good free alternative to Klaviyo for Shopify?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Systeme.io's free plan supports 2,000 contacts with unlimited email sends, full automation sequences (including abandoned cart and welcome flows), funnels, and CRM — all at $0. Klaviyo charges $150–$400/month for the same contact volumes. For stores not relying on Klaviyo's advanced ecommerce segmentation, Systeme.io handles every core email marketing use case for free."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How much does Klaviyo cost per month in 2026?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Klaviyo's pricing in 2026 is based on active profiles: free up to 250 contacts, $20/month for 500, $45/month for 1,000, $150/month for 5,000, $400/month for 15,000, and $700/month for 30,000. Following their February 2025 billing change, Klaviyo charges for all active profiles whether or not you email them, which significantly increased costs for most stores."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can Systeme.io replace Klaviyo abandoned cart emails?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Systeme.io supports abandoned cart email automations on its free plan. You connect Shopify to Systeme.io via Make.com or a native integration, then trigger email sequences based on cart events. The automation builder supports time delays, conditional logic, and multiple follow-up emails — the same capabilities Klaviyo provides for this workflow."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does Klaviyo have that Systeme.io does not?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Klaviyo has deeper native Shopify integration with predictive analytics, advanced revenue attribution per campaign, SMS marketing (built-in), product recommendation blocks, and A/B testing at scale. Systeme.io does not include SMS or predictive LTV analytics. For stores using Klaviyo primarily for email automation flows, Systeme.io covers every use case. For stores relying heavily on Klaviyo's predictive segmentation, the paid tool has value."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How long does it take to migrate from Klaviyo to Systeme.io?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Approximately 30 minutes for most stores. The process involves exporting your Klaviyo contact list as CSV, importing to Systeme.io, and rebuilding your key automation flows. The full migration guide is at stackarchitect.xyz/replace-klaviyo-free. Most stores migrate 3–5 flows (welcome, abandoned cart, post-purchase, win-back, browse abandonment) in a single session."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
