<body>
<Nav />

<!-- NAV -->

<main id="main-content">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero bg-grid" aria-label="Klaviyo vs Systeme.io for Shopify">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
        <ol style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--text-4);">
          <li><a href="https://stackarchitect.xyz/" style="color:var(--text-4);text-decoration:none;">Home</a></li>
          <li aria-hidden="true" style="color:var(--border);">/</li>
          <li style="color:var(--text-3);">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <div class="hero-dateline">Updated March 2026 · Email marketing comparison · Shopify</div>
      <div class="hero-proof">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        <span class="hero-proof-stars" aria-label="5 stars">★★★★★</span>
        <span class="hero-proof-txt">Verified by 500+ Shopify stores &nbsp;·&nbsp; Save $400/month</span>
      </div>
      <h1 itemprop="headline">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io<br><span class="green">The Free Klaviyo</span><br><span class="dim">Alternative That Works.</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub" itemprop="description">Klaviyo changed its billing model in February 2025 and now charges for every active profile — whether you email them or not. <strong>Systeme.io's free plan replaces Klaviyo entirely for most Shopify stores: 2,000 contacts, unlimited emails, full automation flows, $0 forever.</strong></p>

      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-pill"><div class="cost-v" style="color:var(--red);">$150–$400/mo</div><div class="cost-l">Klaviyo at 5–15k contacts</div></div>
        <div class="cost-pill"><div class="cost-v" style="color:var(--g);">$0/mo</div><div class="cost-l">Systeme.io free plan</div></div>
        <div class="cost-pill"><div class="cost-v">2,000</div><div class="cost-l">Free contacts</div></div>
        <div class="cost-pill"><div class="cost-v">Unlimited</div><div class="cost-l">Email sends</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="trust-row">
        <span class="trust-item"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#00c864" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>Abandoned cart flows included</span>
        <span class="trust-item"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#00c864" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>Welcome sequences included</span>
        <span class="trust-item"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#00c864" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>Post-purchase flows included</span>
        <span class="trust-item"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#00c864" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>Migrate in ~30 minutes</span>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="#comparison" class="btn-outline" onclick="event.preventDefault();document.getElementById('comparison').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})">See Full Comparison <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg></a>
        <a href="/go/systeme" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="btn pulse">Try Systeme.io Free <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg></a>
      </div>

      <div class="stat-strip" style="max-width:680px;margin:32px auto 0;">
        <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-v">$400/mo</div><div class="stat-l">Klaviyo at 15k contacts</div></div>
        <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-v">$0</div><div class="stat-l">Systeme.io free plan</div></div>
        <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-v">~30 min</div><div class="stat-l">Migration time</div></div>
        <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-v">$4,800</div><div class="stat-l">Saved per year</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
  <section style="padding:60px 24px;background:var(--bg-3);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);" aria-labelledby="answer-h">
    <div style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="tag tag-dim" style="display:inline-flex;margin-bottom:16px;">Quick Answer</span>
      <h2 id="answer-h" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(20px,3.5vw,30px);letter-spacing:-.03em;color:var(--text);line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:20px;">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io — Which Should You Use for Shopify?</h2>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">For most Shopify stores under 2,000 active email contacts, <strong style="color:var(--text);">Systeme.io is the better choice</strong> — it costs $0 versus Klaviyo's $150–$400/month, and covers every core email automation use case including abandoned cart, welcome sequences, post-purchase flows, and broadcast campaigns.</p>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;">Klaviyo's February 2025 billing change means stores now pay based on all active profiles — including subscribers who haven't been emailed recently. This significantly increased effective costs for stores with large but partially inactive lists. Systeme.io charges based on actual active contacts and never charges per-send.</p>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;">Klaviyo retains an advantage for stores using advanced predictive segmentation, SMS marketing, or deep Shopify revenue attribution per campaign. If those specific features drive your email strategy, Klaviyo is justified. If your goal is running high-performing automation flows at zero cost, Systeme.io is the clear winner.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- KLAVIYO PRICING -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="klaviyo-pricing-h">
    <div class="inner" style="max-width:860px;">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <span class="tag tag-dim" style="margin-bottom:16px;display:inline-flex;">What You're Paying</span>
        <h2 id="klaviyo-pricing-h">Klaviyo Pricing in 2026 — The Full Picture</h2>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;max-width:720px;margin:0 auto 32px;text-align:center;">In February 2025, Klaviyo changed from charging per active email subscriber to charging for all active <em>profiles</em> — meaning anyone in your list, emailed or not. This change increased effective monthly costs for most Shopify stores.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(140px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-bottom:40px;">
        {[
          { contacts: "250", price: "Free", note: "Hard limit" },
          { contacts: "500", price: "$20/mo", note: "" },
          { contacts: "1,000", price: "$45/mo", note: "" },
          { contacts: "5,000", price: "$150/mo", note: "" },
          { contacts: "15,000", price: "$400/mo", note: "" },
          { contacts: "30,000", price: "$700/mo", note: "" },
        ].map(t => (
          <div style="border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:16px 12px;background:var(--bg-3);text-align:center;">
            <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-4);margin-bottom:6px;">{t.contacts}</div>
            <div style="font-weight:900;font-size:18px;color:var(--red);letter-spacing:-.02em;">{t.price}</div>
            {t.note && <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-4);margin-top:4px;">{t.note}</div>}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div style="background:rgba(255,100,100,.06);border:1px solid rgba(255,100,100,.2);border-radius:10px;padding:20px 24px;max-width:680px;margin:0 auto;">
        <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--red);margin-bottom:8px;">⚠ Feb 2025 Billing Change</div>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.7;margin:0;">Klaviyo now charges for <strong style="color:var(--text);">all active profiles</strong>, not just subscribers you've emailed. If your list includes customers, past buyers, and form submitters you haven't contacted in months, you're paying for all of them. Most stores saw an effective 20–40% price increase following this change.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPARISON TABLE -->
  <section class="section-alt" id="comparison" aria-labelledby="comp-h">
    <div class="inner" style="max-width:900px;">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <span class="tag tag-dim" style="margin-bottom:16px;display:inline-flex;">Side-by-side comparison</span>
        <h2 id="comp-h">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io — Full Feature Comparison</h2>
        <p>Every email marketing feature that matters for Shopify stores, compared directly.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="overflow-x:auto;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid var(--border);">
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:14px;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background:var(--bg-3);">
              <th style="padding:14px 20px;text-align:left;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-4);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">Feature</th>
              <th style="padding:14px 20px;text-align:center;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-4);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">Klaviyo</th>
              <th style="padding:14px 20px;text-align:center;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">Systeme.io Free</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ["Monthly cost (2,000 contacts)", "$45–$150/mo", "$0 forever"],
              ["Free contact limit", "250", "2,000"],
              ["Email sends", "Per-send limits", "Unlimited"],
              ["Automation flows", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Abandoned cart emails", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Welcome sequences", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Post-purchase flows", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Broadcast campaigns", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Email templates", "✓", "✓"],
              ["Sales funnels", "Add-on / integration", "✓ (built-in)"],
              ["CRM", "Limited", "✓ (built-in)"],
              ["Affiliate management", "✗", "✓ (built-in)"],
              ["SMS marketing", "✓ (paid add-on)", "✗"],
              ["Predictive analytics (CLV)", "✓", "✗"],
              ["A/B testing", "✓", "Limited"],
              ["Advanced Shopify segmentation", "✓", "Via Make.com"],
              ["Revenue attribution per flow", "✓", "✗"],
              ["Contract / lock-in", "Monthly or annual", "None"],
              ["Data ownership", "Klaviyo platform", "Your Systeme.io account"],
            ].map((row, i) => (
              <tr style={`border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);background:${i % 2 === 0 ? 'transparent' : 'rgba(255,255,255,.015)'};`}>
                <td style="padding:13px 20px;color:var(--text-3);font-size:13px;">{row[0]}</td>
                <td style="padding:13px 20px;text-align:center;color:var(--text-4);font-size:13px;">{row[1]}</td>
                <td style="padding:13px 20px;text-align:center;color:var(--g);font-weight:600;font-size:13px;">{row[2]}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW TO MIGRATE -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="migrate-h">
    <div class="inner" style="max-width:860px;">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <span class="tag tag-dim" style="margin-bottom:16px;display:inline-flex;">Migration guide</span>
        <h2 id="migrate-h">How to Switch From Klaviyo to Systeme.io in 30 Minutes</h2>
        <p>Three steps. No developers. Full migration guide at <a href="https://stackarchitect.xyz/replace-klaviyo-free" style="color:var(--g);">stackarchitect.xyz/replace-klaviyo-free</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-grid">
        <div class="how-step">
          <div class="how-n">Step 01</div>
          <h3 class="how-title">Export Your List</h3>
          <p class="how-body">Export your Klaviyo subscriber list as CSV. Keep active subscribers and segment by engagement. Import directly into Systeme.io — the format maps automatically. Takes 5 minutes.</p>
          <span class="how-tool">Klaviyo → CSV → Systeme.io</span>
        </div>
        <div class="how-step" style="border-left:1px solid var(--border);border-right:1px solid var(--border);">
          <div class="how-n" style="color:var(--sky)">Step 02</div>
          <h3 class="how-title">Rebuild Your Flows</h3>
          <p class="how-body">Recreate your 3–5 core automation flows in Systeme.io's visual builder: welcome sequence, abandoned cart, post-purchase, win-back. Most stores complete all flows in under 20 minutes.</p>
          <span class="how-tool">Systeme.io Automation Builder</span>
        </div>
        <div class="how-step">
          <div class="how-n" style="color:var(--vio)">Step 03</div>
          <h3 class="how-title">Connect Shopify</h3>
          <p class="how-body">Connect Shopify to Systeme.io via Make.com or the native Shopify integration. New customers and orders trigger your automation flows automatically. Cancel Klaviyo and save $150–$400/month immediately.</p>
          <span class="how-tool">Shopify + Systeme.io</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- VERDICT -->
  <section style="padding:60px 24px;background:var(--bg-3);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);" aria-labelledby="verdict-h">
    <div style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="tag" style="display:inline-flex;margin-bottom:16px;">Verdict</span>
      <h2 id="verdict-h" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(22px,4vw,34px);letter-spacing:-.03em;color:var(--text);line-height:1.05;margin-bottom:20px;">Klaviyo vs Systeme.io — Our Recommendation</h2>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;"><strong style="color:var(--g);">Switch to Systeme.io if:</strong> You are paying Klaviyo $150+/month and your primary use is welcome sequences, abandoned cart, and post-purchase emails. You are under 2,000 active contacts or want to reduce your list to that level. You want to eliminate a recurring expense that offers diminishing returns after core flows are set up.</p>
      <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:24px;"><strong style="color:var(--text-4);">Stay on Klaviyo if:</strong> You actively use predictive LTV analytics for campaign decisions, run SMS alongside email from the same platform, or rely on Klaviyo's revenue attribution reports to justify marketing spend to stakeholders.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/go/systeme" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="btn pulse">Try Systeme.io Free →</a>
        <a href="https://stackarchitect.xyz/replace-klaviyo-free" class="btn-outline">Full Migration Guide →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA STRIP -->
  <div class="cta-strip">
    <div class="cta-strip-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="cta-strip-title">Stop paying Klaviyo <span style="color:var(--red)">$150–$400/month.</span></div>
